h3. Summary
In *Service Desk* and *Software* projects on JIRA 7.0, adding the {{jira.issue.editable=false}} property to a step in the workflow only removes the "Edit" button, but allows for inline-editing of any field.

h3. Expected Behavior
The property should impede any editing from happening on issues from projects of any type.

h3. Actual Behavior
Inline-editing is allowed for any field on *Software* and *Service Desk* projects.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a *Software* or *Service Desk* project;
# Add the {{jira.issue.editable=false}} property to any step of the workflow used by that project, then publish the draft;
# Create an issue under that project and transition it to the status where that property was added;
# Notice it's possible to inline-edit any field;

h3. Workaround
Use the {{jira.permission.edit.denied}} property (with no value) instead.

