According to the [An introduction to project centric navigation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/An+introduction+to+project+centric+navigation#expander-control-416955697] documentation:
{quote}
"7. Where are my builds, source and review links?
Links to these pages have been removed from JIRA, as the relevant information is available per issue in the Development panel. When viewing an issue, the Development panel is available on the right-hand side."
{quote}

Even though this information is available in the Development panel, some customers prefer to view this information on project navigation instead of accessing issues to gather this information. By doing this, they don't need to know which ticket has a link, it will show a list of all tickets instead. 
It would be useful to be able to view this information using Project Centric Navigation, so we can have the best of both worlds.

